	<text id="ruskin_to_mother_july_26_1867">
	    
	    <header>
	        <inventNo>1996L00322</inventNo>
	    </header>
	
	    <body>
	        <div type="text">
	            <pb n="1"/>           
	            <opener>
	                <date when="1867-07-26"><!-- match letter exactly, delete if unnecessary -->
	                    <rs type="date">26th July. 1867</rs>
	                </date>
	                <salute>My dearest <rs key="47637407" type="person">Mother</rs></salute><!-- match letter exactly, delete if unnecessary -->
	            </opener>
	            
	            <p id="p1">
	                <s id="s1">I have your nice line; but am very sorry you are so nervous.</s>
	                <s id="s2">I think this is a thing which can <add hand="#JR" place="above">be,</add>and ought to be, avoided.</s>
	                <s id="s3">Merely resolving to let the house take care of itself for a fortnight and absolutely not allowing any one to ask you a question- (and sending <rs key="ann_strachan" type="person">Ann</rs>, who would be unmanageable under such circumstances, to the seaside-) - letting <rs key="76205504" type="person">Joanna</rs> order dinner, and living- for the fortnight- upstairs- and seeing <hi rend="underline">no</hi> one. </s>
	                <s id="s4">You would thus recover calm, and confidence in yourself.</s> 
	                <s id="s5">I am in <pb n="2"/>hopes however that having <rs key="76205504" type="person">Joanna</rs> at home will make a <add hand="#JR" place="above">great</add>difference - only she <hi rend="underline">ought</hi> to be wanted soon in <rs key="Q27" type="place">Ireland</rs>, and you know, we <hi rend="underline">must</hi> get into the way of sparing her.</s>
	            </p>
	            
	            <p id="p2">
	                <s id="s6">You must forgive the nonsense I write to her.</s> 
	                <s id="s7">You will get <hi rend="underline">some</hi> good of the letters. and I couldn't write at all, if they were to be "serious"</s>
	            </p>
	
	            <closer>
	                <salute>Ever my dearest <rs key="47637407" type="person">mother</rs> your most <expan>affect<ex>
						ionat</ex>e</expan> Son</salute><!-- optional - delete if unnecessary -->
	                <signed><!-- optional - delete if unnecessary -->
	                    <rs key="73859585" type="person">J Ruskin</rs>
	                </signed>
	             </closer>
	             
	             <ab id="ab1"> 
	             	<s id="s8"><rs key="Q1025076" type="place">Keswick</rs> <rs type="date">26th July 1867</rs></s>
	             </ab>
	        </div>
	    </body>
